They are excellent, but they do have a different sound; dry, analytical, but
without bipolar harshness. They use the Transnova circuit designed by Jim
Strickland. I have XL series Hafler amps, and I'm very fond of them as well.

I prefer the Transnova type amps, such as the P7000, for speakers with
soft-dome tweeters. For hard dome speakers, I prefer the DH/XL series.

